25|$|The holy day {{is celebrated}} with an all-night vigil on <b>the</b> eve <b>of</b> <b>the</b> feast, and a celebration <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Divine <b>Liturgy</b> <b>the</b> next morning, at which beeswax candles are blessed. This blessing {{traditionally}} takes {{place after the}} Little Hours and before <b>the</b> beginning <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Divine <b>Liturgy</b> (though in some places it is done after). The priest reads four prayers, and then a fifth one during which all present bow their heads before God. He then censes the candles and blesses them with holy water. The candles are then distributed {{to the people and}} <b>the</b> <b>Liturgy</b> begins.|$|R
