2500|$|The Yashts (from yešti, [...] "worship by praise") are a {{collection}} of 21 hymns, each dedicated to a particular divinity or divine concept. Three hymns <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Yasna <b>liturgy</b> that [...] "worship by praise" [...] are—in tradition—also nominally called yashts, but are not counted among the Yasht collection since the three are a part <b>of</b> <b>the</b> primary <b>liturgy.</b> <b>The</b> Yashts vary greatly in style, quality and extent. In their present form, they are all in prose but analysis suggests that they may at one time have been in verse.|$|R
